CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February, 28, 1953, pg. 17 reads: "Birthday Testimonial for Mrs. Robert L. Vann Is Tremendous! - "Mrs. Vann Receives "Wonder Bar" From Special Gift Committee...Mrs. Vann, thriled and happy over her special gift, is shown surrounded by some of the sponsors who made it possible. At her left is Mrs. Alma Polk,  Others in picture include William G. Nunn, WIlliam A. Pryor, Mrs. O.M. Walton, Mrs. Cora B. Matthews, Charles Lewis, the Rev. James B. Cayce, Lois Lee Dorsey, Earsley Kincaid, Thomas West, Willa Mae Rice, Frank Lavelle, the Rev. Charles H. Foggie, P.L. Prattis, Mrs. Alma Illery and Dr. Don Jefferson."
TitMainTitle: Jessie Vann, standing at open case of barware, surrounded by Bill Nunn Sr., Maudelina Johnson, Rev. Charles Foggie, Lois Lee Dorsey, Reverend James Casey, Elizabeth McCombs, Alma Polk, Alma Illery, and Dr. Don Jefferson, in interior with sunburst patterned curtains and band in background, for birthday testimonial for Jessie Vann, possibly Syria Mosque
